textBeforeTable: Patent Citations Finally, the wicking action can have a dual purpose in that the wick material can provide a filter media for separating components of a liquid or fluid, in addition to being a sterility barrier for a sterilized needle or lance. One such example of the wicking material acting as a filtering media may be where the wicking material separates certain components of the blood from other components of the blood, by way of example and for purposes of illustration and not to be construed as limiting of the present material. The wicking material can serve more than one purpose, such as wicking for transporting of fluid to chemistry such as a reagent strip, but also can serve as a filter, as well as a sterility barrier. FIGS. 22a and 22b illustrate a flow chart including corresponding column entries to graphics of FIG. 2; events; audio beeps, as well as visual displays corresponding to the electronics of FIG. 5; and the duration, as well as application notes. The events, as well as the display duration and application notes, are explanatory in operation of the medical system or measurement system. The system performance chart provides for operational events of the system. The wicking unit 648 can include the adhesive-back foil which stabilizes the enzyme in the reagent.
